<hr class="classref-item-separator"/>

<a id="NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData2D_method_add_projected_obstruction"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

`void` **add_projected_obstruction**\ (\ vertices\: [PackedVector2Array](PackedVector2Array.md), carve\: [bool](bool.md)\ ) [ðŸ”—](#NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData2D_method_add_projected_obstruction)

Adds a projected obstruction shape to the source geometry. If `carve` is ``true`` the carved shape will not be affected by additional offsets (e.g. agent radius) of the navigation mesh baking process.

[Rect2](Rect2.md) **get_bounds**\ (\ ) [ðŸ”—](#NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData2D_method_get_bounds)

Returns all the obstructed area outlines arrays.

<hr class="classref-item-separator"/>

<a id="NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData2D_method_get_projected_obstructions"></a>

<!-- classref-method -->

[Array](Array.md) **get_projected_obstructions**\ (\ ) <span class="const">const</span> [ðŸ”—](#NavigationMeshSourceGeometryData2D_method_get_projected_obstructions)

Returns the projected obstructions as an [Array](Array.md) of dictionaries. Each [Dictionary](Dictionary.md) contains the following entries:

- ``vertices`` - A [PackedFloat32Array](PackedFloat32Array.md) that defines the outline points of the projected shape.

- ``carve`` - A [bool](bool.md) that defines how the projected shape affects the navigation mesh baking. If ``true`` the projected shape will not be affected by addition offsets, e.g. agent radius.

<hr class="classref-item-separator"/>
